   <h2>About The PMA</h2>
   <h3> “Majestic space with famed entry staircase featuring
      Renaissance classics & special exhibits”</h3>
   <p>The Philadelphia Museum of Art is an art museum originally
      chartered in 1876 for the Centennial Exposition in Philadelphia.
      The main museum building was completed in 1928 on Fairmount,
      a hill located at the northwest end of the Benjamin Franklin
      Parkway at Eakins Oval.</p>
